{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"7c6b1860-dbab-4797-a290-d90ce02612e8","content":"To switch from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform, make these changes in your project file:\n\n1. **Remove** (or set to `false`) the VSTest opt-in:\n   ```xml\n   <!-- Delete this line -->\n   <UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>\n   ```\n\n2. That's it for `MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0` — Microsoft.Testing.Platform is the **default** runner when `UseVSTest` is not set to `true`.\n\n### Key differences to be aware of\n\n| | VSTest | Microsoft.Testing.Platform |\n|---|---|---|\n| Run tests | `dotnet test` | `dotnet test` (still works) or run the test exe directly |\n| CLI options | `--filter`, `--logger`, etc. | `--filter`, `--report-trx`, etc. (slightly different flags) |\n| `.runsettings` | Fully supported | Supported, but some adapter-specific nodes may differ |\n\n### If you use CI / `dotnet test`\n`dotnet test` works with both runners. No pipeline changes are usually needed, but if you pass VSTest-specific logger flags (e.g. `--logger trx`), replace them:\n\n```bash\n# Before (VSTest)\ndotnet test --logger trx\n\n# After (Microsoft.Testing.Platform)\ndotnet test --report-trx\n```\n\n### Quick checklist\n- [ ] Remove `<UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>`\n- [ ] Search your repo/CI for VSTest-specific CLI flags and update them\n- [ ] Run `dotnet test` to verify everything passes","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"ea045ae5-0eae-40e6-9053-919a07c6cffd","outputTokens":381,"requestId":"7C1E:12D387:25FEF8E:2A0F754:69F93FA4"},"id":"581f8e97-1a7c-48ea-8d22-aa12c2056dc4","timestamp":"2026-05-05T00:54:05.056Z","parentId":"ea69f696-4aa6-40ec-9fb6-a59404bbda9b"}
